'''Mallasvesi''' is a medium-sized lake in [[Finland]]. The lake is part of the [[Kokem<U+00E4>enjoki]] basin and it is located for municipalities of [[P<U+00E4>lk<U+00E4>ne]] and [[Valkeakoski]] in the [[Pirkanmaa]] region. It is a part of a chain of lakes that begins from the lakes [[Lummene]], [[Vehkaj<U+00E4>rvi]] and [[Vesijako]] at the [[drainage divide]] between the [[Kokem<U+00E4>enjoki]] and [[Kymijoki]] basins and flows westwards trough lakes [[Kukkia]], [[Iso-Roine]], [[Hauhonselk<U+00E4>]] and [[Ilmoilanselk<U+00E4>]]. <ref name=jw>[http://www.jarviwiki.fi/w/index.php?title=Mallasvesi_%2835.711.1.001%29&setlang=en Mallasvesi in the Jarviwiki Web Service]. Retrieved 2014-03-07. {{en icon}}</ref>

